HEADWORD: Tingis
<hw>Tin"gis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small hemipterous insects which
injure trees by sucking the sap from the leaves. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

